io.github.msdk.spectra.peakinvestigator

Class PeakInvestigatorScanExtractingMethod

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.msdk.spectra.peakinvestigator.PeakInvestigatorScanExtractingMethod
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MSDKMethod<List<MsSpectrum>>

    public class PeakInvestigatorScanExtractingMethod
extends Object
implements MSDKMethod<List<MsSpectrum>>
    This class extracts scans from the results returned from PeakInvestigator. Internally, it returns a SimpleMsSpectrum object if no error bars are present. Otherwise, it returns a PeakInvestigatorMsSpectrum, which decorates a SimpleMsSpectrum.

      • parseMsSpectrum

        protected MsSpectrum parseMsSpectrum(BufferedReader reader)
                              throws IOException
        This function assumes that the data is either formatted as two columns or five columns, separated by whitespace. If two columns, a MsSpectrum is returned via MSDKObjectBuilder.getMsSpectrum(). If five columns, the simple MsSpectrum is decorated using the PeakInvestigatorMsSpectrum.
        Parameters:
        reader - a BufferedReader object.
        Returns:
        a MsSpectrum object.
        Throws:
        IOException - if any.
